igh levels, even during waterlogging. Igap?? species have a fast initial growth and constant leaf production, investing in high seed mass, leaf sclerophylly and reduced leaf loss. They tend to remain in a state of rest during flooding. ?? 2001 Elsevier Science B.V.},
